TITLE: Implementing Basic Export Function in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows a simple implementation of an export function for Dexie.js databases. It exports all tables and their rows in a transaction.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dexie/Dexie.js/blob/master/addons/dexie-export-import/README.md#2025-04-16_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function export(db) {
    return db.transaction('r', db.tables, ()=>{
        return Promise.all(
            db.tables.map(table => table.toArray()
                .then(rows => ({table: table.name, rows: rows})));
    });
}
```

